The '''Great Northern Arts Festival''' is held each year in [[Inuvik, Northwest Territories]]. Lasting approximately ten days, it is an annual event held each summer. It was established in 1989 by Sharlene Alexander and Sue Rose. While the festival's mandate is to serve Northern artists and craftspeople, artists from around the world also attend.<ref name="gnaf">{{cite web|url=http://www.gnaf.org/|title=The Great Northern Arts Festival|work=gnaf.org|accessdate=18 May 2010}}</ref> The festival is designed as a venue for artists to see each other's work and to experiment with new applications. It includes arts of all types, such as [[fiber art]]<ref name="Thomas">{{cite book|last1=Thomas|first1=Nancy |last2=Rabinowitz|first2=Ilana |last3=Falick|first3=Melanie |title=A passion for knitting: step-by-step illustrated techniques, easy contemporary patterns, and essential resources for becoming part of the world of knitting|url=https://books.google.com/?id=bmgsuAiAlooC&pg=PA185&dq=%22Great+Northern+Arts+Festival%22#v=onepage&q=%22Great%20Northern%20Arts%20Festival%22&f=false|year=2002 |publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=0-684-87069-X|page=185}}</ref> and [[Music of the Northwest Territories]]. Artists partake in demonstrations, masterclasses, seminars, and workshops.<ref>{{cite book|last=Grace|first=Sherrill E. |title=Canada and the Idea of North|url=https://books.google.com/?id=GVF2fVGBe8EC&pg=PA25&dq=%22Great+Northern+Arts+Festival%22#v=onepage&q=%22Great%20Northern%20Arts%20Festival%22&f=false|year=2001|publisher=McGill-Queen's Press|isbn=0-7735-2247-6|page=25}}</ref> The festival's gallery offers pieces for sale. There are cultural presentations each evening which include concerts, dance, fashion, music, and storytelling.<ref name="yukoninfo">{{cite web|url=http://www.yukoninfo.com/inuvik/info/gnaf.htm|title=The Great Northern Arts Festival|work=yukoninfo.com|accessdate=18 May 2010}}</ref> Media coverage brings festival highlights to viewing audiences.<ref name="Beckett">{{cite book|last=Beckett|first=Harry |title=Nunavut|url=https://books.google.com/?id=GVF2fVGBe8EC&pg=PA25&dq=%22Great+Northern+Arts+Festival%22#v=onepage&q=%22Great%20Northern%20Arts%20Festival%22&f=false|series=Eye on Canada series|year=2003|publisher=Weigl Educational Publishers|isbn=1-894705-02-5|page=25}}</ref>
